<h2>What Does a Professional Website Cost in Kenya?</h2>
<p>If you're a Kenyan business owner searching for a web designer, the first question on your mind is probably cost. Website design in Kenya ranges from <strong>Ksh 8,000 for a basic template site</strong> up to <strong>Ksh 150,000+ for a fully custom build</strong>. At Tupate Studio, we build hand-coded, custom websites from <strong>Ksh 25,000</strong> — delivered in under two weeks.</p>
<p>But price alone doesn't tell you much. This guide walks you through everything you need to know: what to expect, what questions to ask, and how to avoid wasting money on a website that doesn't work.</p>

<h2>Why Your Business Needs a Website in 2024</h2>
<p>Over <strong>22 million Kenyans</strong> are active internet users. When someone hears about your business — whether from a friend, a flyer, or a WhatsApp message — the first thing they do is Google you. If they can't find you, or they find a slow, outdated page, they move on to a competitor.</p>
<p>A professional website does three things for your business:</p>
<ul>
  <li><strong>Builds credibility</strong> — customers trust businesses with a real web presence</li>
  <li><strong>Generates leads 24/7</strong> — your website works while you sleep</li>
  <li><strong>Ranks on Google</strong> — so customers find you without you spending on ads</li>
</ul>

<h2>Types of Websites for Kenyan Businesses</h2>
<h3>1. Brochure / Business Website</h3>
<p>A 4–8 page website that introduces your business, lists your services, and includes a contact form. Best for: consultants, clinics, law firms, agencies. Cost: <strong>Ksh 25,000 – 45,000</strong>.</p>

<h3>2. E-commerce Website</h3>
<p>An online store with a product catalogue, shopping cart, and M-Pesa payment integration. Best for: retailers, manufacturers, fashion brands. Cost: <strong>Ksh 45,000 – 120,000</strong>. If you are considering an older site, a <a href="/articles/business-website-redesign-kenya">website redesign Kenya</a> is often the fastest way to modernise your digital presence.</p>

<h3>3. Landing Page</h3>
<p>A single-page site optimised to convert visitors into enquiries or buyers. Best for: product launches, ad campaigns. Cost: <strong>Ksh 12,000 – 25,000</strong>.</p>

<h3>4. Corporate / Enterprise Website</h3>
<p>A large, multi-section website with staff profiles, project portfolios, and custom integrations. Best for: NGOs, large companies, universities. Cost: <strong>Ksh 80,000+</strong>. See our dedicated guide to <a href="/articles/corporate-website-design-kenya">corporate website design Kenya</a> for what these builds require.</p>

<h3>5. Niche / Industry-Specific Website</h3>
<p>Specialised websites built around industry requirements. Examples include an <a href="/articles/industrial-business-website-kenya">industrial machinery website Kenya</a> designed as a procurement tool, a <a href="/articles/medical-dental-website-kenya">medical clinic website Kenya</a> optimised for patient trust and appointment booking, a <a href="/articles/law-firm-website-kenya">law firm website Kenya</a> built around professional credibility signals, a <a href="/articles/real-estate-website-kenya">real estate website Kenya</a> with property listing functionality, a <a href="/articles/restaurant-hotel-website-kenya">restaurant website Kenya</a> with digital menu and direct booking, and a <a href="/articles/school-college-website-kenya">school website Kenya</a> covering admissions, fees, and curriculum.</p>

<h2>What to Look for in a Kenyan Web Designer</h2>
<p>Before you pay a deposit, ask these questions:</p>
<ol>
  <li><strong>Do you build custom or use templates?</strong> — Templates are faster but limit your SEO and performance.</li>
  <li><strong>Will my site be fast on mobile?</strong> — Over 80% of Kenyan web traffic is mobile. A slow site loses customers.</li>
  <li><strong>Who owns the website after it's built?</strong> — You should own your domain, hosting, and all files.</li>
  <li><strong>Will it rank on Google?</strong> — Ask about on-page SEO, page speed, and schema markup.</li>
  <li><strong>What's included in the price?</strong> — Hosting, domain, SSL, email setup, and edits vary by agency.</li>
</ol>

