<h2>Common Mistakes Kenyan Businesses Make with Their Websites</h2>
<ul>
  <li><strong>Choosing the cheapest option</strong> — A Ksh 5,000 template site looks cheap and ranks poorly.</li>
  <li><strong>Not owning their domain</strong> — Some agencies register the domain in their name. Always own your own.</li>
  <li><strong>No SEO setup</strong> — A beautiful site no one can find is wasted money.</li>
  <li><strong>Ignoring mobile speed</strong> — Kenyan users are on 4G/3G. Every second of load time costs you customers.</li>
  <li><strong>No contact mechanism</strong> — Always have a visible phone number, WhatsApp link, and contact form.</li>
</ul>

